flowRoot.flowPara: While, we rely on purchases to fund development, there are no costly fees, confusing user agreements, trial periods, or restrictive copy protections. You can install it on as many computers as you want or even copy it and give it away to your friends.
elementary relies on the support of users like you.

text.tspan: A fast and free replacement for Windows and OS X

flowRoot.flowPara: We believe that computers can be easy, fun, and gorgeous. By putting design first, we ensure we're not compromising on quality or usability.
Engineered from the ground up to be light on it’s toes, It starts up quickly, logs in instantly, and uses the bare minimum of resources so that your apps enjoy a speed boost as well.
Our code is developed in the open, meaning it's available for review, scrutiny, modification, and redistribution by anyone. No hidden agendas or unfair stifling of competition.
Rip, Sync, Shuffle, Pause, and pick up where you left off. Life has a soundtrack; Music plays it.
Rip, Sync, Shuffle, Pause, and pick up where you left off. Life has a soundtrack; Music plays it.

All different kinds of people from all over the world build elementary OS, so it’s no surprise that it's built with this in mind. It comes stocked with apps and tweaks for the hearing and sight impaired, and well as assistance for the motor impaired.

It's is built on the rock-solid foundation of Linux (the same software that powers the U.S Department of Defense, the Bank of China, and more). It has no known viruses, which means no pesky anti-virus software to slow down your system.
